<subSubSection id="04B6D9C7FFDAC912FF27888382617002" pageId="31" pageNumber="270" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="4C138A4CFFDAC912FF27888382617002" blockId="31.[174,779,1760,1816]" pageId="31" pageNumber="270">
<emphasis id="7ED8565EFFDAC912FF278883804671E2" bold="true" box="[174,293,1760,1784]" pageId="31" pageNumber="270">Etymology</emphasis>
: The specific epithet (Latin, adjective) alludes to the massive spines in the internal sac of the aedeagus.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="04B6D9C7FFDAC912FF27895C85287662" pageId="31" pageNumber="270" type="description">
<paragraph id="4C138A4CFFDAC912FF27895C80477082" blockId="31.[174,779,1855,2104]" pageId="31" pageNumber="270">
<emphasis id="7ED8565EFFDAC912FF27895C8050704D" bold="true" box="[174,307,1855,1879]" pageId="31" pageNumber="270">Description</emphasis>
: External characters as in 
<taxonomicName id="8BACF1CFFFDAC912FD0889238267704D" authorityName="Assing &amp; Brachat &amp; Meybohm" authorityYear="2019" box="[641,772,1856,1879]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Cephennium" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="31" pageNumber="270" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sinuosum">
<emphasis id="7ED8565EFFDAC912FD0889238267704D" box="[641,772,1856,1879]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="270">C. sinuosum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; distinguished only by the male primary sexual characters.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="4C138A4CFFDAC912FF2789C280C27F22" blockId="31.[174,779,1855,2104]" pageId="31" pageNumber="270">
♂: aedeagus 
<quantity id="8B5427A9FFDAC912FED989C380D370AD" box="[336,432,1952,1976]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.7" pageId="31" pageNumber="270" unit="mm" value="0.27">0.27 mm</quantity>
long; ventral process much broader, shorter, and apically less acute in ventral view, stouter in lateral view; internal sac with a long and massive median spine and with three pairs of lateral spines (
<figureCitation id="D49796C9FFDAC912FF76864380F67F22" box="[255,405,2080,2104]" captionStart="Figs 114–126" captionStartId="13.[174,214,2004,2026]" captionTargetBox="[179,1418,260,1982]" captionTargetId="figure-120@13.[174,1421,255,1994]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="Figs 114–126: Cephennium spp.of the C. sinuosum group:C. sinuosum (114–117), C. fortespinosum (118–119), C. hamulatum (120– 121), C. curvatum (122), C. selenanum (123–124), and C. latius (125–126): habitus (114); aedeagus in lateral and in ventral view (115–126). Scale bars: 114: 0.5 mm; 115–126: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4755266" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4755266/files/figure.png" pageId="31" pageNumber="270">Figs 118–119</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="4C138A4CFFDAC912FCB98E9C85287662" blockId="31.[816,1421,255,376]" pageId="31" pageNumber="270">
<emphasis id="7ED8565EFFDAC912FCB98E9C85667602" bold="true" box="[816,1029,255,280]" pageId="31" pageNumber="270">Comparative notes</emphasis>
: 
<taxonomicName id="8BACF1CFFFDAC912FB9F8F63845A7602" authorityName="Assing &amp; Brachat &amp; Meybohm" authorityYear="2019" box="[1046,1337,256,280]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Cephennium" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="31" pageNumber="270" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fortespinosum">
<emphasis id="7ED8565EFFDAC912FB9F8F63845A7602" box="[1046,1337,256,280]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="270">Cephennium fortespinosum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is reliably distinguished from 
<taxonomicName id="8BACF1CFFFDAC912FBC98F4385A2762D" authorityName="Assing &amp; Brachat &amp; Meybohm" authorityYear="2019" box="[1088,1217,288,311]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Cephennium" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="31" pageNumber="270" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sinuosum">
<emphasis id="7ED8565EFFDAC912FBC98F4385A2762D" box="[1088,1217,288,311]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="270">C. sinuosum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and other species of the 
<taxonomicName id="8BACF1CFFFDAC912FCFF8F238294764D" authorityName="Assing &amp; Brachat &amp; Meybohm" authorityYear="2019" box="[886,1015,320,343]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Cephennium" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="31" pageNumber="270" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sinuosum">
<emphasis id="7ED8565EFFDAC912FCFF8F238294764D" box="[886,1015,320,343]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="270">C. sinuosum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group only by the shape and internal structures of the aedeagus.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="04B6D9C7FFDAC912FCB98FFC82F7752D" pageId="31" pageNumber="270" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="4C138A4CFFDAC912FCB98FFC82F7752D" blockId="31.[816,1421,415,568]" pageId="31" pageNumber="270">
